main event: A UFO sighting occurred in Irondequoit, New York, on 23rd June 1959, lasting approximately 30 minutes. The object was described as a silent, bluish-white bubble or sphere that appeared to remain stationary.
interesting points: The UFO was described as resembling a white, bubble-like object with a tapered tail or appendage, traveling east.

The witness suggested that the object's behavior was characteristic of a meteor or similar celestial phenomenon, citing its rapid motion, twisting course, and lack of light, sound, or smoke as typical of meteors entering the Earth's atmosphere.
The witness reported extremely rapid and zigzagging motion of the object, along with its apparent path towards the northern sky before making an indistinct turn and bank.
The witness was a 35-year-old male with three years of college education and a job as a Chemical Marine Inspector.

The object was not reported to any official, and the case was listed as inconclusive due to the close similarity to an undescribed phenomena involving reflecting radar waves, despite the reported visual sighting.
sighted object: silent, bluish-white bubble-like object with a tapered tail or appendage
